# Scan Execution Architecture

The following diagram illustrates how the [run_full_scan.ps1](file:///c:/llm-security-lab/scripts/run_full_scan.ps1) orchestrator interacts with the individual security tools and the local Ollama instance during a full test run.

```mermaid
graph TD
    Orchestrator[run_full_scan.ps1]
    
    subgraph Security Scanners
        G[Garak]
        P[PyRIT]
        A[Augustus]
    end
    
    Ollama[Ollama / Target Model]
    
    subgraph Generated Reports
        G_Rep[(garak_results.json)]
        P_Rep[(pyrit_results.json)]
        A_Rep[(augustus_results.json)]
    end
    
    FinalReportScript[generate_final_report.py]
    Final_JSON[(final_security_report.json)]

    Orchestrator -->|Runs| G
    Orchestrator -->|Runs| P
    Orchestrator -->|Runs| A
    
    G -->|Scans| Ollama
    P -->|Scans| Ollama
    A -->|Scans| Ollama
    
    G -->|Outputs| G_Rep
    P -->|Outputs| P_Rep
    A -->|Outputs| A_Rep
    
    G_Rep -->|Aggregated by| FinalReportScript
    P_Rep -->|Aggregated by| FinalReportScript
    A_Rep -->|Aggregated by| FinalReportScript
    
    FinalReportScript --> Final_JSON
```
